</p><p>
<b><i>Euler's totient function</i></b> &#966;(<i>n</i>)=20
is the number of positive integers not exceeding <i>n</i> that have <nobr>n=
o common</nobr> divisors with <i>n</i>=20
(other than the common divisor 1).

</p><p>
In other words, &#966;(<i>n</i>) is the number of integers <i>m</i> coprime=
 to <i>n</i> such that 1 &#8804; <i>m</i> &#8804; <i>n</i>.
<br>
(Note that the number 1 is counted as coprime to all positive integers incl=
uding itself.)


</p><pre><b>SOME TEST CASES FOR EULER'S TOTIENT FUNCTION:</b>
&#966;(1) =3D 1       &#966;(100) =3D 40
&#966;(2) =3D 1       &#966;(9007199254740881) =3D 9007199254740880
&#966;(20) =3D 8      &#966;(9007199254740997) =3D 9007199254740996
&#966;(36) =3D 12     &#966;(999999999999999999) =3D 441994921381739520
&#966;(81) =3D 54     &#966;(9999999999999999999) =3D 6666666666666666660
&#966;(90) =3D 24     &#966;(99999999999999999999) =3D 58301444908800000000
</pre>


